# JavaScript Code Style & Standards

## General JavaScript Guidelines

- Use modern ES6+ features (async/await, arrow functions, destructuring)
- Follow functional programming patterns where appropriate
- Use meaningful variable names and clear function documentation
- Prefer `const` over `let`, avoid `var`
- Use template literals for string interpolation
- Add JSDoc comments for complex functions

## Chrome Extension APIs

- Use Manifest V3 APIs exclusively
- Prefer `chrome.storage.sync` for user preferences (cross-device sync)
- Use `chrome.storage.local` for temporary data (like block counts)
- Always handle async operations with proper error handling
- Use `declarativeNetRequest` for blocking (not deprecated webRequest)

## Common Patterns

- Use `chrome.storage.onChanged` for real-time UI updates
- Implement domain validation with URL constructor
- Follow Chrome extension lifecycle patterns (onInstalled, etc.)

## Error Handling

- Always wrap async operations in try-catch blocks
- Provide fallback values for storage operations
- Log errors to console for debugging
- Gracefully handle storage quota exceeded scenarios
